owl:Ontology.terms:description:
The semanticscience integrated ontology (SIO) provides a simple, integrated ontology (types, relations) for objects, processes and their attributes.
This project provides foundational support for the Bio2RDF (http://bio2rdf.org) and SADI (http://sadiframework.org) projects.
website: http://semanticscience.org email: sio-ontology@googlegroups.com mailing list: http://groups.google.com/group/sio-ontology
owl:Ontology.terms:rights: free to use,share,modify. modify with attribution [http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/].
owl:Ontology.terms:title: Semanticscience Integrated Ontology (SIO)
owl:Ontology.schema:comment:
general class inclusion axioms: 'is part of' some 'physical entity' subClassOf 'is located in' some 'physical entity'
role chains: 'has capability' o 'is realized in' -> 'is participant in'

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: cites is a relation to refer to by way of example, authority or proof.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: cites

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A contains B iff the spatial region occupied by A has the spatial region occupied by B as a part, and B is not part of A. [T]
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: contains

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: denotes is a relation between an entity and what it is a sign or indication of, or what specifically means.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: the symbol '%' denotes a proportion in relation to a whole.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: denotes

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a derives to b if and only if a or some part thereof is consumed in the formation of b.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: derives into

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: describes is a relation between one entity and another entity that it provides a description (detailed account of).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: describes

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A relation between two objects, in which the first object contains information that is used to produce the second object.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: an open reading frame encodes a protein (it contains information that specifies the amino acid composition and topology)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: encodes

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: exists at is a relation between an entity and a time measurement.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: exists at

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has agent is a relation between a process and an entity, where the entity is present throughout the process and is a causal participant in the process.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has agent

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has annotation is a relation between an entity and some textual anntotation.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: document x is annotated with the keywords 'ontology','semantic web'
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has annotation

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has attribute is a relation that associates a entity with an attribute where an attribute is an intrinsic characteristic such as a quality, capability, disposition, function, or is an externally derived attribute determined from some descriptor (e.g. a quantity, position, label/identifier) either directly or indirectly through generalization of entities of the same type.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has attribute

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has basis is a relation between a realizable entity and the quality that forms the basis for it.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: the solubility of salt (the disposition) is based on the molecular structure of NaCl (the quality) that allows the polarized water-molecules (the trigger) to break the ion bonds (the realization).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has basis

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has boundary is a mereological relation between a whole and boundary located at its periphery.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: the surface of an apple is a 2D boundary of the apple.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has boundary

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has capability is a relation between an entity and the capability that it bears.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: SIO has the capability to semantically integrate data.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has capability

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has component part is a relation between a whole and a component part where the component is instrinsic to the whole, and loss of the part would change the kind that it is.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a human has blood as a component part
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has component part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A has concretization B iff A is an informational entity and B is the a quality of some material entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has concretization

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has creator is a relation between an entity and that which created it.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: the iPhone was created by Apple Inc
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has creator

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has data item is a relation between a dataset and any described / referrenced entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has data item

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has direct part is a relation to specify a part at a particular level of granularity
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a car has an engine as a direct part
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has direct part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has disposition is the relation between an entity and a disposition that it bears.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has disposition

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has evidence is a relation between a proposition and something that demonstrates the truth of the assertion.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has evidence

owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: the story 'war of worlds' is expressed as every language edition of the book 'war of the worlds'
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has expression

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has first part is a proper part relation in which the part is the first of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has first part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has frequency is a relation that specifies the occurence of an object or event
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has frequency

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has function is the relation between an entity and a function that is ascribed to it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has function

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a relation between an entity and an identifier.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has identifier

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has implementation is a relation between a specification and an implementation that conforms to it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has implementation

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has input is a relation between a process and an entity, where the entity is present at the beginning of the process.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has input

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has last part is a proper part relation in which the part is the last of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has last part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has measurement value is a relation between a quality/realizable and a measurement value.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has measurement value

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has member is a mereological relation between a collection and an item.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a collection of cars has as a car as a member
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has member

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has ordered part of is a proper part relation in which the part is one of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has ordered part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has output is a relation between an process and an entity, where the entity is present at the end of the process.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has output

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has parameter is a relation between a process and an information content entity which modulates the behaviour of some participant.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has parameter

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has part is a transitive, reflexive and antisymmetric relation between a whole and itself or a whole and its part.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a collection of cars has as a car as a part;a car has an engine as a part; a car has a piston as a part;
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has participant is a relation that describes the participation of the object in the (processual) subject.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has participant

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has phenotype is a relation between an object and an observable/measurable characteristic.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has phenotype

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has product is a relation between an process and an entity, where a new entity exists at the end of the process.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has product

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has proper part is an antisymmetric, irreflexive (normally transitive) relation between a whole and a distinct part.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a car has an engine as a proper part; a car has a piston as a proper part;
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has proper part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has property is a relation between an entity and the quality, capability or role that it and it alone bears.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: michel's hair has the quality of being brown in colour.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has property

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is provided by is a relation between an entity and the entity that provides it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has provider

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has quality is a relation between an entity and the quality that it bears.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has quality

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has role is a relation between an entity and a role that it bears.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has role

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has source is a relation between an entity and another entity from which it stems from.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has source

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has substrate is a relation between a process and an object where the object is destroyed by its participation in the process.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has substrate

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has target is a relation between a process and an entity, where the entity is present at the beginning of the process and undergoes a change or transformation in the process.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has target

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has trigger is a relation between a realizable and the factor that causes it to be realized.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has trigger

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has unique identifier is an inverse functional relation between an entity and an identifier that uniquely identifies it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has unique identifier

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has unit is a relation between a quantity and the unit it is a multiple of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has unit

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a immediately derives into b if and only if a or some significant part thereof is consumed in the formation of b and there are no identifiable intermediate entities between a and b.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: immediately derives into

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A non-transitive temporal relation in which one process immediately precedes another process, such that there is no interval of time between the two processes.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: immediately precedes

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A temporal relation in which an entity mainstains identity from one state to another.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: immediately transforms into

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a in relation from b is a comparative relation in a is the object of reference in a relation with b.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: in relation from

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: in relation to is a comparative relation to indicate that the instance of the class holding the relation exists in relation to another entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: in relation to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is about is a relation between an information content entity and the entity that its primary subject.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is about

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is adjacent to B iff there is a small, but non-zero distance between A and B
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is adjacent to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is agent in is a relation between an entity and a process, where the entity is present throughout the process, no permanent material change occurs, and is a causal participant in the process.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: hexokinase is an agent in the conversion of glucose to glucose-6-phosphate
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is agent in

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is alternate of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is annotation of is a relation between some textual entity and the entity that it annotates.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is annotation of

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: x is associated with y when x and y are logically or statistically related to one another.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is associated with

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is attribute of is a relation that associates an attribute with an entity where an attribute is an intrinsic characteristic such as a quality, capability, disposition, function, or is an externally derived attribute determined from some descriptor (e.g. a quantity, position, label/identifier) either directly or indirectly through generalization of entities of the same type.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is attribute of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is base for is a relation between a quality and the realizable entity that it is the basis for.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is base for

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is boundary of is a mereological relation between a boundary located at the periphery of a whole.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is boundary of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is causally related with

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is cited by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is comparable to is a relation between two entities that share at least one feature whose value can be compared.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is comparable to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is component part of is a relation between a component and a whole, where the component is instrinsic to the whole, and loss of the part would change the kind that the whole is.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is component part of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is contained in

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: x is correlated with y when x holds a statistical relationship with y
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is correlated with

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is covalently connected to is a relation between an atom and another atom.

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is creator of is a relation between a creator and an entity..
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is creator of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: 'is data item in' is a relation between an entity that is described or referenced in a dataset.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is data item in

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A transitive temporal relation in which one entity was materially formed from another non-identical entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is derived from

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is described by is a relation between one entity and another entity that provides a description (detailed account) of it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is described by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is direct part of is a relation between a specific part (at some level of granularity) and its whole.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is direct part of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is directly after is a relation between entities placed on a dimensional axis in which the projection of the position of the first entity is numerically greater than the projection of the position of the second entity, and the entities are adjacent to one another.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is directly after

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is directly before is a relation between entities placed on a dimensional axis in which the projection of the position of the first entity is numerically less than the projection of the position of the second entity, and the entities are adjacent to one another.

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is directly connected to B iff there exists a path direclty between A and B.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is directly connected to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is disposition of is a relation between a disposition and the entity that it is a property of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is disposition of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has disputing evidence is a relation between a proposition and something that disputes (does not directly support) the truth of the assertion.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is disputed by

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is dissimilar to

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is equal to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is expression of is a relation between more concrete expression of some conceptualization.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: every language edition of 'war of the worlds' are expressions of the story of 'war of the worlds'
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is expression of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is first part of is a proper part relation in which the part is the first of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is first part of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is frequency of is a relation between a temporal unit and an object or event
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is frequency of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is function of is a relation between a function and an entity that it is a property of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is function of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is generalization of is a relation between a more general instance (in terms of spatial/temporal localization & other attributres) than the other.

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is generically related with B iff A is an abstract entity or an information content entity and B is a information content entity or a physical entity, respectively.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is identical to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a relation between an identifier and an entity.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is input in

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is greater than to is a comparison relation between two quantities in which the first has a value smaller or equal to the second.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is measurement value of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is member of is a mereological relation between a item and a collection.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is member of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a is mutual role of b if and only if the realization of role a necessarily causes the realization of role b.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is mutual role of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a is mutually related to b if and only if the realization of the relation of a necessarily causes the realization of a relation to b.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is mutually related to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is narrower than B iff the meaning of term A is narrower in scope than the meaning of term B
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is narrower than

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is narrower than B (t) iff for A is narrower than B.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is narrower than (t)

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is numerically comparable to is a comparison relation between two quantities whose datatype value can be compared.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is numerically comparable to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is ordered part of is a proper part relation in which the part is one of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is ordered part of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is orthologous to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is reference for is a relation between a document that provides information about an entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is referenced by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is referred to by B iff B is an informational entity that makes reference to A.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is referred to by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has evidence is a relation between a proposition and something that refutes (is incompatible with) the truth of the assertion.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is refuted by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is related to B iff there is some relation between A and B.
owl:ObjectProperty.schema:comment: 'is related to' is the top level relation in SIO
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is related to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is represented by: a relation between an entity and some symbol.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is represented by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is role of is a relation between a role and the entity that it is a property of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is role of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is similar to is a relation between two entities that share one or more features.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is similar to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is source of is a relation between a source of information about some entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is source of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is spatiotemporally related to B iff A is in the spatial or temporal vicinity of B
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is spatiotemporally related to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is specialization of is a relation between a more specific instance (in terms of spatial/temporal localization & other attributres) than the other.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a weather forecast for the city of London produced at a specific time is a specialization of a weather forecast for the city of London.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is specialization of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a relation between a product and the information content entity that specifies it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is specified by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is subsequent version of B iff A is a variant of B and A derives from B.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is subsequent version of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is supported by is a relation between a proposition and something that supports the truth of the assertion.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is supported by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A 'is surrounded by' B iff the A 'is contained by' B and A 'is adjacent to' B or A 'is directly connected to' B.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is surrounded by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is target in is a relation between an entity and a process, where the entity is present at the beginning of the process and undergoes a change or transformation in the process.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: glucose is a target in the hexokinase-mediated conversion of glucose to glucose-6-phosphate.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is target in

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a relation between two information content entities in which one is transcribed into (an exact or similar kind) another through some process.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: DNA is transcribed into RNA
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is transcribed into

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A transitive temporal relation in which an entity mainstains identity from one state to another.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is transformed from

owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: RNA is translated into Protein
a relation between two information content entities in which one is translated into (a completely different kind of entity) another through some process.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is translated into

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is unique identifier for is a relation between an identifier and an entity that it uniquely identifies
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is unique identifier for

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is unit of is a relation between a unit and a quantity that it is a multiple of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is unit of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is variant of: a relationship indicating that two entities are different (by some measure), but either achieve the same objectives in different ways or are permutations of one another (temporal, logical or otherwise)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is variant of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is version of is a relation that holds between any two versions in which one is a subsequent or alternate version of (through a branch).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is version of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is weakly interacting with is a symmetric relation between two molecular entities (or any part thereof) that are interacting through some weak force (van der waals, hydrogen bonds, electrostatic interactions)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is weakly interacting with (transitive)

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a relation between two entities which indicates their common ancestry but due to horizontal gene transfer.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is xenologous to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: measured at is a relation between a measurement value and the time measurement.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: measured at

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: x negatively regulates y if and only if x is a process and y is either a process or a quality, and the progression of x exerts an reduced effect on the frequency, rate or extent of y
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: negatively regulates

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A overlaps with B iff there is some C that is part of both A and B. [S][R]
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: overlaps with

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: x positively regulates y if and only if x is a process and y is either a process or a quality, and the progression of x exerts an effect that increases the frequency, rate or extent of y
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: positively regulates

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A transitive, temporal relation in which one process precedes (has occured earlier than) another process.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: precedes

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: realizes is a relation between a process and a realizable entity (role, function, disposition).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: realizes

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: references is a relation between one entity and the entity that it makes reference to by name, but is not described by it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: references

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: refers to is a relation between one entity and the entity that it makes reference to.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: refers to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: x regulates y if and only if x is a process and y is either a process or a quality, and the progression of x exerts an effect on the frequency, rate or extent of y
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: regulates

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a represents b when a serves as a sign, symbol or model of b.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: represents

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: satisfies is a relation between an entity and the specification or objective that it conforms to.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: satisfies

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A relation between an information content entity and a product that it (directly/indirectly) specifies
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: specifies

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A 'surrounds' B iff the A 'contains' B and A 'is adjacent to' B or A 'is directly connected to' B.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: surrounds

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A transitive temporal relation in which an entity mainstains identity from one state to another.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: transforms into

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:description: A relation between a informational entity and its actual value (numeric, date, text, etc).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has value

owl:Class.terms:description: A quality that has a value that is outside normal or average.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: abnormal

owl:Class.terms:description: aborted is a process status in which a started process will not complete as intended.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: aborted

owl:Class.terms:description: An abstract role is a role whose basis lies in spatial/temporal or comparative relations.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: abstract role

owl:Class.terms:description: An abstract section is a document section that provides brief summary of a document that explains the main argument(s), topic(s) or findings.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: abstract section

owl:Class.terms:description: An academic is an individual that participates in education and scholarship.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: academic

owl:Class.terms:description: An academic department is a division of a university or school faculty devoted to a particular academic discipline.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: academic department

owl:Class.terms:description: An academic organization is a lawfully recognized organization that confers diplomas, degrees and other forms of recognition of academic achievement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: academic organization

owl:Class.terms:description: An academic role is a social role that pertains to the academic institution.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: academic role

owl:Class.terms:description: An acid is a molecular entity in solution capable of donating a hydron (Bronsted acid) or capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron pair (Lewis acid).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: acid

owl:Class.terms:description: An acid-base reaction is a chemical reaction between an acid and a base.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: acid-base reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: An acknowledgements section is a document section that identifies individuals, groups or organizations for their support in the development of the work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: acknowledgements section

owl:Class.terms:description: An action specification is a specification composed of a sequence of instructions to achieve some objective.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: action specification

owl:Class.terms:description: A molecular activator is a molecular regulator that realizes its disposition to conformationally change a target molecule and increase its functionality.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: activator

owl:Class.terms:description: The role of a chemical entity that increases the rate of reaction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: activator role

owl:Class.terms:description: An active ingredient is a molecular entity that exhibits biological activity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: active ingredient

owl:Class.terms:description: active movement is the process in which an object is spatially displaced using some chemical energy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: active movement

owl:Class.terms:description: An active site is a molecular site in which a chemical event occurs (structural transformation or conformational change).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: active site

owl:Class.terms:description: active transport is the movement of a substance across a membrane against its concentration gradient (from low to high concentration) and requires chemical energy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: active transport

owl:Class.terms:description: An addition reaction is an organic reaction where two or more molecules combine to form a larger one. Addition reactions are limited to chemical compounds that have multiply-bonded atoms: * Molecules with carbon-carbon double bonds or triple bonds * Molecules with carbon - hetero double bonds like C=O or C=N
owl:Class.rdfs:label: addition reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: An address is a position that indicates the physical location of some entity using a social convention.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: address

owl:Class.terms:description: An administrative role is the role of an individual that performs administrative tasks for some organization.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: administrative role

owl:Class.terms:description: affection is an emotion characterized with a feeling or type of love for another living thing.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: affection

owl:Class.terms:description: An affiliation is a social relation which indicates the partnership between two or more entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: affiliation

owl:Class.terms:description: age is the length of time that a person has lived or a thing has existed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: age

owl:Class.terms:description: aggregate of carbon nanorods is an allotrope of carbon considered to be the least compressible material known, as measured by its isothermal bulk modulus; aggregated diamond nanorods have a modulus of 491 gigapascals (GPa), while a conventional diamond has a modulus of 442 GPa. ADNRs are also 0.3% denser than regular diamond.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: aggregated carbon nanorods

owl:Class.terms:description: agreement is the result of consensus decision making when members of the group agree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: agreement

owl:Class.terms:description: agreement quality is a quality that exhibits the degree of consensus for some set of assertions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: agreement quality

owl:Class.terms:description: An algorithm is an effective method expressed as a finite list of well-defined instructions for calculating a function.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: algorithm

owl:Class.terms:description: alive is the state of a biological organism that exhibits biological functions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: alive

owl:Class.terms:description: An allele is one of a set of sequence variants of a gene.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: allele

owl:Class.terms:description: An allosteric site is a binding site that when bound to particular ligand changes the conformational state and affects its functionality.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: allosteric site

owl:Class.terms:description: An allotrope is a structural variant of a chemical element.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: allotrope

owl:Class.terms:description: An alpha helix is structural region of a protein that is characterized by 3.6 residues per turn, a translation of 1.5 angstroms along the helical axis in which backbone N-H groups form a hydrogen bond to the backbone carboxyl group of the amino acid four residues prior.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: alpha helix

owl:Class.terms:description: Altitude is a distance above sea level.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: altitude

owl:Class.terms:description: always indicates that the event occurs at all times.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: always

owl:Class.terms:description: An amino acid is an organic molecule composed of a carbon bonded to four different groups: a carboxyl group, an amino group, an R group, and a hydrogen atom. In the case of glycine, the R group is another hydrogen atom.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: amino acid

owl:Class.terms:description: An amino acid residue is a part of a molecule that is derived from an amino acid molecule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: amino acid residue

owl:Class.terms:description: amorphous carbon is an allotrope of carbon that does not have any crystalline structure. As with all glassy materials, some short-range order can be observed, but there is no long-range pattern of atomic positions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: amorphous carbon

owl:Class.terms:description: Anabolism is the set of metabolic processes that construct larger chemical entities units from smaller chemical entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: anabolism

owl:Class.terms:description: an analyte is a substance or chemical constituent of interest in an analytical procedure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: analyte

owl:Class.terms:description: an anatomical entity is an object that is a structural part (material or immaterial) of a biological entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: anatomical entity

owl:Class.terms:description: anger is disgust directed toward an equal status individual.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: anger

owl:Class.terms:description: angst is the intense feeling of apprehension, anxiety or inner turmoil.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: angst

owl:Class.terms:description: An anion is an atom or molecule with a net negative electrical charge.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: anion

owl:Class.terms:description: An annotation is a written explanatory or critical description, or other in-context information (e.g., pattern, motif, link), that has been associated with data or other types of information.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: annotation

owl:Class.terms:description: Annoyance is an unpleasant emtion that is characterized by a abnormal or excessive sensitivity to some external stimulus.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: annoyance

owl:Class.terms:description: An answer is a reply to a question.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: answer

owl:Class.terms:description: An antibody (also known as immunoglobulins, abbreviated Ig) are gamma globulin proteins that are used by the immune system to identify and neutralize foreign objects. They are typically made of two large heavy chains and two small light chains.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: antibody

owl:Class.terms:description: An antigen is a chemical entity that can be bound by a major histocompatibility complex (MHC) and presented to a T-cell receptor.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: antigen

owl:Class.terms:description: antiport enabled secondary active transport is a secondary active transfort in which both ion and molecule are transported in opposite directions simultaneously.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: antiport enabled secondary active transport

owl:Class.terms:description: An antonym is a word with opposite or nearly opposite meaning.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: antonym

owl:Class.terms:description: anxiety is an emotion charactersized by intense feeling of fear and concern coupled with a physical response.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: anxiety

owl:Class.terms:description: An apartment number is the number assigned to identify an apartment in a building of apartments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: apartment number

owl:Class.terms:description: apathy is an emotion characterized by lack of interest, enthusiasm, or concern.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: apathy

owl:Class.terms:description: apprehension is the negative emotion that something unpleasant will occur.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: apprehension

owl:Class.terms:description: an arc is a closed segment of a differentiable curve.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: arc

owl:Class.terms:description: area is a quantity that pertains to the extent of a two-dimensional surface or shape, or planar lamina, in the plane.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: area

owl:Class.terms:description: An argument is a set of one or more declarative sentences (or propositions) known as the premises along with another declarative sentence (or proposition) known as the conclusion.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: argument

owl:Class.terms:description: An aromatic bond is an interaction between a set of atoms across which pairs of electrons are shared.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: aromatic bond

owl:Class.terms:description: An aromatic ring is a ring in which the electrons are delocalized across all atoms in the ring.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: aromatic ring

owl:Class.terms:description: arousal is an emotion characterized by state of reactive to stimuli. It involves the activation of the reticular activating system in the brain stem, the autonomic nervous system and the endocrine system, leading to increased heart rate and blood pressure and a condition of sensory alertness, mobility and readiness to respond.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: arousal

owl:Class.terms:description: An arrowed line is a directed line segment in which one or both endpoints is tangentially part of a triangle that bisects the line.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: arrowed line segment

owl:Class.terms:description: An article is a publication that is stand-alone section of a larger work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: article

owl:Class.terms:description: The aspect ratio of a geometric shape is the ratio of its sizes in different dimensions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: aspect ratio

owl:Class.terms:description: An assay is an investigative (analytic) procedure in laboratory medicine, pharmacology, environmental biology, and molecular biology for qualitatively assessing or quantitatively measuring the presence or amount or the functional activity of a target entity (the analyte) which can be a drug or biochemical substance or a cell in an organism or organic sample.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: assay

owl:Class.terms:description: An assertion ovopub is an ovopub that contains and links to an assertion subgraph with one or more statements that may be true or false, as well as statements describing its provenance.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: assertion ovopub

owl:Class.terms:description: An assertional qualifier is the quality of affirmation, either being positive or negative.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: assertional qualifier

owl:Class.terms:description: An assocation is a relationship between two or more entities derived by some informational analysis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: association

owl:Class.terms:description: An atom is composed of a core of protons and/or neutrons which may be surrounded by a cloud of electrons.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: atom

owl:Class.terms:description: An attribute is a characteristic of some entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: attribute

owl:Class.terms:description: An audio recording is an electrical or mechanical inscription and re-creation of sound waves, such as spoken voice, singing, instrumental music, or sound effects.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: audio recording

owl:Class.terms:description: An author contribution section is a document section that describes the contribution of the authors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: author contribution section

owl:Class.terms:description: an ordered list of authors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: author list

owl:Class.terms:description: An author role is the role of an individual that creates a creative, written work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: author role

owl:Class.terms:description: An author section is a document section that lists the contributing authors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: author section

owl:Class.terms:description: awe is an emotion produced by that which is grand, sublime or powerful and is characterized by a combination of joy, fear and admiration/reverence/respect.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: awe

owl:Class.terms:description: An axis is a line segment that is part of a statistical graph in which the position along the line corresponds to a numeric or categorical value.
owl:Class.schema:comment: The value of a plotted geometric objects (e.g. point) can be obtained from the perpendicular projection of the position of the object onto the axis. Axis may also be associated with a textual description of what the values on the axis represents.
owl:Class.resource:example: The left vertical and bottom horizontal lines with tickmarks in Graph 1 http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A bar is a rectangle that is located in the plot of a statistical graph in which its length is proportional to the values that it represents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bar

owl:Class.terms:description: A bar graph is a statistical graph with rectangular bars of lengths proportional to that value that they represent.
owl:Class.resource:example: Graphs 3,4,5 in http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bar graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A base is a molecular entity dissolved in a solvent that is capable of accepting a proton (Bronsted base) or forming a covalent bond with a hydron (Lewis base) .
owl:Class.rdfs:label: base

owl:Class.terms:description: A base pair is a weak molecular interaction composed of hydrogen bonds between nucleobases.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: base pair

owl:Class.terms:description: A base stack is a stabilizing interaction of DNA and RNA between spatially adjacent nucleotides and possibly involving London dispersion, hydrophobic and electrostatic forces.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack

owl:Class.terms:description: Behaviour is the set of actions and mannerisms made by systems (biological or otherwise) in response to stimuli or inputs, whether internal or external, conscious or subconscious, overt or covert, and voluntary or involuntary.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: behaviour

owl:Class.terms:description: A belief is a proposition that is believed to be true.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: belief

owl:Class.terms:description: bent is the quality of a line being sharply curved or having an angle.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bent

owl:Class.terms:description: A beta strand is structural region of a protein that is characterized by a roughly planar sequence of amino acid residues forming hydrogen bonds between the N-O and the C=O of another part of the peptide and having their side chains perpendicular to the planar axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: beta strand

owl:Class.terms:description: A bibliography section is a document section that is composed of a list of references used in the development of the work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bibliography section

owl:Class.terms:description: A bill is proposed legislation under consideration by a legislature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bill

owl:Class.terms:description: A binary compound is a mereological maximum sum of two kinds of weakly connected entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: binary compound

owl:Class.terms:description: A binary scale is a measurement scale that specifies a choice between two values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: binary scale

owl:Class.terms:description: A binding site is a molecular site which when occupied with particular ligands leads to structural transformations that initiatiate new moelcular processes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: binding site

owl:Class.terms:description: biochemical activation is a molecular interaction that increases the catalytic rate of the target enzyme.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biochemical activation

owl:Class.terms:description: biochemical inhibition is a molecular interaction that decreases the catalytic rate of the target enzyme.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biochemical inhibition

owl:Class.terms:description: A biochemical pathway specifies a series of biochemical modifications and transformations towards achieving some biological outcome.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biochemical pathway

owl:Class.terms:description: A biochemical reaction is a biochemical process that involves the conversion of at least one chemical participant (target) into another (product) by an enzyme (agent).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biochemical reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: bioinformatic data is data genereated or used for computer-based investigations of biological phenomena.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bioinformatic data

owl:Class.dc:description: A biologic, also known as a biologic medical product, biological, or biopharmaceutical, is any pharmaceutical drug product manufactured in, extracted from, or semisynthesized from biological sources.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biologic

owl:Class.terms:description: biological data is scientific data relevant to biology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological data

owl:Class.terms:description: A biological entity is a heterogeneous substance that contains genomic material or is the product of a biological process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A biological fluid is a fluid of biological origin.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological fluid

owl:Class.terms:description: A biological quality is a quality held by a biological entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological quality

owl:Class.terms:description: biological reproduction is the biological process by which one or more biological organisms are produced from their "parents".
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological reproduction

owl:Class.terms:description: biological sex is the quality of a biological organism based on reproductive function or organs.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological sex

owl:Class.terms:description: A biomolecular structure descriptor is structure description for organic compounds.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biomolecular structure descriptor

owl:Class.terms:description: A biopolymer is an organic polymer using biological components.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biopolymer

owl:Class.terms:description: A sequence is a primary structure descriptor in which each of the letters in the string represents a monomeric unit (residue) in which adjacent letters represent the connectivity between the monomeric units.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biopolymer sequence

owl:Class.terms:description: biosynthesis is the synthesis of an organic compound in a living organism, usually aided by enzymes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biosynthesis

owl:Class.terms:description: birthing is the process by which a biological organism is brought into existence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: birthing

owl:Class.terms:description: A block histogram contains an x-axis that is divided into bins which correspond to value ranges. Each item in the data set is drawn as a rectangular block, and the blocks are piled into the bins to show how many values in each range.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: block histogram

owl:Class.terms:description: A blog is a publication accessible at some website and is typically about various experiences.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: blog

owl:Class.terms:description: boldness is the trait of being willing to undertake things that involve risk or danger.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: boldness

owl:Class.terms:description: A book is a publication composed of a large number of entries.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: book

owl:Class.terms:description: A book series is a collection of books that have been sequentially published.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: book series

owl:Class.terms:description: A book volume is a book that is part of a collection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: book volume

owl:Class.terms:description: A booklet is a document that lacks a named publisher or sponsoring institution.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: booklet

owl:Class.terms:description: boredom is the emotion experience by those not interested in their surroundings or available activities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: boredom

owl:Class.terms:description: A bottom value axis is a value axis that is spatially positioned to the bottom of the plot area.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bottom value axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A boxplot (box-and-whisker diagram) is a convenient way of graphically depicting groups of numerical data through their five-number summaries: the smallest observation (sample minimum), lower quartile (Q1), median (Q2), upper quartile (Q3), and largest observation (sample maximum).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: boxplot

owl:Class.terms:description: A brand name is a trademarked and marketed name of a product.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: brand name

owl:Class.terms:description: A brief is a written legal document used in various legal adversarial systems that is presented to a court arguing why one party to a particular case should prevail.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: brief

owl:Class.terms:description: Brownian motion is the seemlingly random movement of particles suspended in a fluid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: brownian motion

owl:Class.terms:description: A bubble chart contains circles whose area corresponds to a value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bubble chart

owl:Class.terms:description: A buffer is a dissolved chemical substance that resists change in pH upon addition of small amounts of acid or base.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: buffer

owl:Class.terms:description: A buffer role is the role of a chemical substance which maintains a pH at a near constant value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: buffer role

owl:Class.terms:description: cancelled is a process status in which the process, while planned to occur, will not occur.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: cancelled

owl:Class.terms:description: A capability is a realizable entity whose basis lies in one or more parts or qualities and reflects possibility of an entity to behave in a specified way under certain conditions or in response to a certain stimulus (trigger).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: capability

owl:Class.terms:description: a carbohydrate is an organic molecule composed of one or more monosaccharides.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbohydrate

owl:Class.terms:description: A carbohydrate residue is a part of a molecule that was derived from a monosaccharide molecule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbohydrate residue

owl:Class.terms:description: A carbon allotrope is a chemical substance composed of carbon.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbon allotrope

owl:Class.terms:description: carbon nanofoam is an allotrope of carbon that consists of a low-density cluster-assembly of carbon atoms strung together in a loose three-dimensional web. Each cluster is about 6 nanometers wide and consists of about 4000 carbon atoms linked in graphite-like sheets that are given negative curvature by the inclusion of heptagons among the regular hexagonal pattern.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbon nanofoam

owl:Class.terms:description: A Cartesian coordinate is the signed distance of a point to some referent line.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: diagnostic test

owl:Class.terms:description: diamond is a carbon allotrope in which each carbon atom in diamond is covalently bonded to four other carbons in a tetrahedron. These tetrahedrons together form a 3-dimensional network of puckered six-membered rings of atoms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diamond

owl:Class.terms:description: A diary is a document which describes day-to-day experiences.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diary

owl:Class.terms:description: A diastereomer is a stereoisomer that is not a mirror image of its isomer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diastereomer

owl:Class.terms:description: A difference in number of objects produced is a count of the number of objects produced with respect to a second variable (space, time, etc)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: difference in number of objects produced

owl:Class.terms:description: A differential diagnosis (sometimes abbreviated DDx, ddx, DD, D/Dx, or ΔΔ) is a systematic diagnostic method used to identify the presence of an entity where multiple alternatives are possible (and the process may be termed differential diagnostic procedure), and may also refer to any of the included candidate alternatives (which may also be termed candidate condition).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: differential diagnosis

owl:Class.terms:description: A differential equation is a mathematical equation for an unknown function of one or several variables that relates the values of the function itself and its derivatives of various orders.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: differential equation

owl:Class.terms:description: A differential gene expression ratio is the ratio of gene expression values from a test sample compared to a control sample.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: differential gene expression ratio

owl:Class.terms:description: diffusion is motion of particles at temperatures above absolute zero.

owl:Class.terms:description: A diffusion equation describes density fluctuations in a material undergoing diffusion.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diffusion equation

owl:Class.terms:description: A dimensional quantity is a quantity that has an associated unit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dimensional quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: A dimensionless quantity is a quantity that has no associated unit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dimensionless quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: A dipole-dipole interaction is a weak submolecular interaction between strongly electronegative atoms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dipole-dipole interaction

owl:Class.terms:description: a directed acyclic graph or DAG is a network digram that contains directed edges in which nodes may have multiple parents, but there are no cycles.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: directed acyclic graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A directed line segment is a line segment that is contained by an ordered pair of endpoints (a start point and an endpoint).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: directed line segment

owl:Class.terms:description:
DisGeNET Disease specificity is a measure of disease coverage. It is calculated from the negative base 2 log of the ratio of number of diseases associated to the total number of diseases.
The measure is described here: http://www.disgenet.org/web/DisGeNET/menu/dbinfo#specificity
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DisGeNET disease specificity

owl:Class.terms:description:
The DisGeNET pleiotropy index is a measure of specificity as it pertains to classes of disease. The disease pleotropy index is computed from the ratio of the number of disease classes associated with an entity over the total number of disease classes multplied by 100.
The measure is defined here: http://www.disgenet.org/web/DisGeNET/menu/dbinfo#pleiotropy
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DisGeNET Pleiotropy Index

owl:Class.terms:description: agreement is the result of consensus decision making when members of the group do not all agree.

owl:Class.terms:description: disappointment is the feeling of dissatisfaction that follows the failure of expectations or hopes to manifest.

owl:Class.terms:description: Discouragement is the emtion of having lost confidence or enthusiasm.

owl:Class.terms:description: disease is the outward manifestation of one or more disorders.

owl:Class.terms:description: Disgust is a feeling of revulsion or profound disapproval aroused by something unpleasant or offensive.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: disgust

owl:Class.terms:description: OR is a logical operator that results in true whenever one or more of its operands are true.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: disjunction (or)

owl:Class.terms:description: disordered is a structural quality in which the parts of an object are non-rigid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: disordered

owl:Class.terms:description: A displacement reaction is an inorganic reaction in which a elementary substance displaces and sets free a constituent atom from a molecule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: displacement reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A disposition is the tendency of a capability to be exhibited under certain conditions or in response to a certain stimulus (trigger).
owl:Class.resource:example: solubility (to dissolve when put in fluid); fragility (disposition to break when dropped)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: disposition

owl:Class.terms:description: A disulfide bond is a bond between two sulfur atoms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: disulfide bond

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene that is located on DNA.

owl:Class.terms:description: A doctor is an individual who practices medicine, which is concerned with promoting, maintaining or restoring human health through the study, diagnosis, and treatment of disease, injury, and other physical and mental impairments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: doctor

owl:Class.terms:description: A doctor role is the role of an individual who practices medicine, which is concerned with promoting, maintaining or restoring human health through the study, diagnosis, and treatment of disease, injury, and other physical and mental impairments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: doctor role

owl:Class.terms:description: A document is a bounded physical or digital representation of a body of information designed with the capacity (and usually intent) to communicate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document

owl:Class.terms:description: A bibliographic attribute is an attribute related to publications.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document component

owl:Class.terms:description: A document section is a component of a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document section

owl:Class.terms:description: A document title is a textual entity that summarizes the topic of the document in one sentence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document title

owl:Class.terms:description: A document version is a version of a work in some sequence of derivative works.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document version

owl:Class.terms:description: A dose is the quantity of a chemical substance administered to a biological system.

owl:Class.terms:description: A double arrowed line is an arrowed line in which both terminal points are tangentially part of different triangles that bisect the line.

owl:Class.terms:description: A double bond is a covalent bond between a pair of atoms in which two pairs of electrons are shared.

owl:Class.terms:description: double stranded nucleic acid is a molecular complex composed of two weakly connected deoxyribonucleic acids.

owl:Class.terms:description: double stranded nucleic acid is a molecular complex composed of two weakly connected nucleic acids.

owl:Class.terms:description: double stranded nucleic acid is a molecular complex composed of two weakly connected ribonucleic acids.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: double stranded RNA

owl:Class.terms:description: draft is the quality of text that has not yet complete.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: draft

owl:Class.terms:description: dread is the instense negative emotion that induces fear and apprehension.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dread

owl:Class.terms:description: A drop line is a statistical graph line that vertically or horizontally connects a data series line with a value axis in a statistical graph.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: drop line

owl:Class.terms:description: A drug is a chemical entity that regulates a biological process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: drug

owl:Class.terms:description: A drug-drug interaction is an interaction in which two drugs interact in such a way to produce a non-additive biological response.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: drug drug interaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A drug regulatory authority is a regulatory authority which acts to control what substances may be used to treat individuals.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: drug regulatory authority

owl:Class.terms:description: dying is a process in which a biological entity ceases to exist.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dying

owl:Class.terms:description: dysfunction is a capability to act in a manner that is abnormal or opposite to the object's typical function.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dysfunction

owl:Class.rdfs:label: e.coli

owl:Class.terms:description: ecstacy is an emotion characterized by a heightened state of consciousness with total involvement of a subject.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ecstasy

owl:Class.terms:description: an edge is a line connecting two graph vertices.

owl:Class.terms:description: An edited publication is a publication that has been examined and potentially changed by an editor.

owl:Class.terms:description: An edition number is count of a literary work edited and published, as by a certain editor or in a certain manner including being printed during some interval of time.

owl:Class.terms:description: effective dose is the amount of a substance required to produce an effect on a predefined percentage of a population.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: effective dose

owl:Class.terms:description: electronic structure is the electron configuration is the distribution of electrons of an atom or molecule (or other physical structure) in atomic or molecular orbitals.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: electronic structure

owl:Class.terms:description: Email message is a digital document that is composed of a header and a body and is transmitted using the SMTP protocol.

owl:Class.terms:description: an email address is an identifier to send mail to particular electronic mailbox.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: email address

owl:Class.terms:description: Embarrassment is the emotion of intense discomfort with oneself, experienced upon having a socially unacceptable act or condition witnessed by or revealed to other.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: embarassment

owl:Class.terms:description: An emotion is a process (experience) that arises internally or from an involuntary physiological response to a stimulus.

owl:Class.terms:description: empty is the quality of not containing some thing

owl:Class.terms:description: An end date is a time instant pertaining to date of the end of a process.

owl:Class.terms:description: An end position is the distal position of an object relative to an origin in a linear system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: end position

owl:Class.terms:description: An end time is a time instant pertaining to the time at which a process ends.

owl:Class.terms:description: An endpoint is a terminal point that is the last of an ordered pair of points.

owl:Class.terms:description: Every thing is an entity.

owl:Class.terms:description: An environment is a geographic region that hosts certain processes or objects.

owl:Class.terms:description: envy is an emotion that occurs when a person lacks another's (perceived) superior quality, achievement or possession and wishes that the other lacked it.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: envy

owl:Class.terms:description: An enzyme is a protein or protein complex that realizes its disposition to covalently modify some molecule during a chemical reaction.

owl:Class.terms:description: An epimer is a stereoisomer that differs in configuration at only one stereogenic center.

owl:Class.terms:description: ethnicity is the biological quality of membership in a social group based on a common heritage.

owl:Class.terms:description: euphoria is an emotion characterized by intense feelings of well-being, elation, happiness, ecstasy, excitement, and joy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: euphoria

owl:Class.terms:description: An evaluation role is a processual role held by an entity during some evaluation.

owl:Class.dc:description: evidence is the body of facts or information indicating whether a belief or proposition is true or valid.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: evolving

owl:Class.terms:description: existence quality is the quality of an entity that describe in what environment it is known to exist.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: experimental protocol

owl:Class.terms:description: false is a truth value in that indicates that it is not true.

owl:Class.terms:description: A group of people affiliated by consanguinity, affinity, or co-residence.

owl:Class.terms:description: a fax number is a number to connect to fax device
owl:Class.rdfs:label: fax number

owl:Class.terms:description: Fear is a negative emotion induced by a perceived threat that induces one to hide or move quickly away from the location of the perceived threat.

owl:Class.terms:description: female is a biological sex of an individual with female sexual organs.

owl:Class.terms:description: fictional is the quality of an entity that exists only in a creative work of fiction.

owl:Class.terms:description: A Gantt chart is a bar chart that illustrates a project schedule.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: gene-disease association

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-disease association in which the disease phenotype is associated with an altered expression of the gene.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gene-disease association linked with altered gene expression

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-variant disease association in which a mutation in the gene/protein results in the development or maintenance of the disease.

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-disease association in which the gene is included in a chromosomal rearrangement associated with a particular manifestation of the disease.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gene-disease association linked with chromosomal rearrangement

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-disease association in which a sequence variation (a mutation, a SNP) is associated with the disease.

owl:Class.terms:description: a gene-disease association that is linked with some genomic alteration

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-variant disease association in which a germline mutation in the gene/protein results in the development or maintenance of the disease, and it may be passed on to offspring.

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-variant disease association in which a germline mutation in the gene modifies the clinical presentation of the disease, and it may be passed on to offspring.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gene-disease association linked with germline modifying mutation

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-disease association in which a gene mutation is known to modify the clinical presentation of the disease.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gene-disease association linked with modifying mutation

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-disease association in which the disease phenotype is associated with post-translational modifications in the protein product.
owl:Class.resource:example: methylation or phosphorylation of protein product
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gene-disease association linked with post-translational modification

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-variant disease association in which a somatic mutation in the gene/protein results in the development or maintenance of the disease, and it may not be passed on to offspring.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gene-disease association linked with somatic causal mutation

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-variant disease association in which a somatic mutation in the gene modifies the clinical presentation of the disease, and it may not be passed on to offspring.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gene-disease association linked with somatic modifying mutation
