owl:Class.terms:description: A sequence profile is provides the preference for a character at each position of an abstracted sequence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequence profile

owl:Class.terms:description: A sequence start position is the start position for a sequence of characters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequence start position

owl:Class.terms:description: A sequence variant role is a comparative role in which the composition of characters in a sequence differs when compared to another entity of similar type.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequence variant role

owl:Class.terms:description: A set is a collection of entities, for which there may be zero members.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: set

owl:Class.terms:description: set item is an item in a set.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: set item

owl:Class.terms:description: severe is a qualitative intensity value that is more intense than strong, but less intense than fatal.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: severe

owl:Class.terms:description: shame is the emotion borne from feeling responsible for the commission of an offense.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: shame

owl:Class.terms:description: shape is the quality of a bearer that relates to its spatial extent.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: shape

owl:Class.terms:description: shock is an emotion of sudden upset or surprise.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: shock

owl:Class.terms:description: shyness is an emotion of apprehension, lack of comfort, or awkwardness experienced when in proximity to, approaching, or being approached by other individuals, especially in new situations or with unfamiliar individuals.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: shyness

owl:Class.terms:description: sick is the status of a living organism that is behaving at a sub-optimal level.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sick

owl:Class.terms:description: A sign language (also signed language) is a language that involves manual communication and body language to convey meaning. This can involve simultaneously combining hand shapes, orientation and movement of the hands, arms or body, and facial expressions to fluidly express a speaker's thoughts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sign language

owl:Class.terms:description: A signal is an object that initiates a sequence of events.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: signal

owl:Class.terms:description: A signal transducer is a molecule that responds to and amplifies a signal in a signalling system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: signal transducer

owl:Class.terms:description: A single arrowed line is directed line in which the endpoint is tangentially part of a triangle that bisects the line.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: single arrowed line segment

owl:Class.terms:description: A single bond is a covalent bond between a pair of atoms in which one pair of electrons are shared.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: single bond

owl:Class.terms:description: A single displacement reaction where one atom is transferred out of one molecule and into another.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: single displacement reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: a single nucleotide variation (SNV) is a nucleotide residue that is a variant compared to some reference nucleic acid sequence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: single nucleotide polymorphism

owl:Class.terms:description: A site is a spatial region bounded (in part or in whole) by material entities and may be occupied by material entities.
owl:Class.resource:example: A nostril; the interior of the heart valve; the interior of a bottle.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: site

owl:Class.terms:description: A slide is an visual representation meant to communicate some information.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: slide

owl:Class.terms:description: A slideshow is a visual presentation of information contained within a collection of slides.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: slideshow

owl:Class.terms:description: A slope or gradient of a line describes its steepness, incline, or grade. A higher slope value indicates a steeper incline. Slope is normally described by the ratio of the "rise" divided by the "run" between two points on a line.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: slope

owl:Class.terms:description: A small cytoplasmic RNA (scRNA) molecule is a small (7S; 129 nucleotides) RNA molecule found in the cytosol and rough endoplasmic reticulum that are normally associated with proteins that are involved in specific selection and transport of other proteins.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: small cytoplasmic RNA (scRNA)

owl:Class.terms:description: A small cytoplasmic RNA (scRNA) gene is a gene that encodes a small (7S; 129 nucleotides) RNA molecule found in the cytosol and rough endoplasmic reticulum that are normally associated with proteins that are involved in specific selection and transport of other proteins.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: small cytoplasmic RNA (scRNA) gene

owl:Class.terms:description: A small nuclear RNA (snRNA) is a small RNA molecule that is located in the nucleus of a cell.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: small nuclear RNA (snRNA)

owl:Class.terms:description: A small nuclear RNA (snRNA) gene is a gene that encodes a small niuclear RNA molecule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: small nuclear RNA (snRNA) gene

owl:Class.terms:description: A small nucleolar RNA (snoRNA) is a small RNA that are associated with the eukaryotic nucleus as components of small nucleolar ribonucleoproteins.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: small nucleolar RNA (snoRNA)

owl:Class.terms:description: A small nucleolar RNA (snoRNA) gene is a gene that encodes a small RNA that are associated with the eukaryotic nucleus as components of small nucleolar ribonucleoproteins.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: small nucleolar RNA (snoRNA) gene

owl:Class.terms:description: A social entity pertains to the interaction among individuals and groups.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: social entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A social relation is a social entity that describes a relationship between two or more individuals or groups.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: social relation

owl:Class.terms:description: A social role is a role that is ascribed to individuals in a community.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: social role

owl:Class.terms:description: A social structure is a social entity which consists of relationships between two or more entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: social structure

owl:Class.terms:description: A software application is software that can be directly executed by some processing unit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software application

owl:Class.terms:description: A software entity is a computational entity that can be interpreted by or directly executed by a processing unit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A software interpreter is a software application that executes some specified input software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software interpreter

owl:Class.terms:description: A software library is software composed of a collection of software modules and/or software methods in a form that can be statically or dynamically linked to some software application.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software library

owl:Class.terms:description: A software method (also called subroutine, subprogram, procedure, method, function, or routine) is software designed to execute a specific task.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software method

owl:Class.terms:description: A software module is software composed of a collection of software methods.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software module

owl:Class.terms:description: A software process identifier is an identifier for a software process in some operating system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software process identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A software script is software whose instructions can be executed using a software interpreter.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software script

owl:Class.terms:description: A software version label is a version label for a piece of software.
owl:Class.resource:example: major.minor[.build[.revision]]
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software version label

owl:Class.terms:description: software execution is the process of executing software on a computing device.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sofware execution

owl:Class.terms:description: A solid-state drive (SSD) is a data storage device that uses solid-state memory to store persistent data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: solid state hard drive

owl:Class.terms:description: A solute is a substance that becomes dissolved in a solvent.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: solute

owl:Class.terms:description: A solvent is a substance that can dissolve other substances (solutes).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: solvent

owl:Class.terms:description: some refers to in the minority of occasions
owl:Class.rdfs:label: some of the time

owl:Class.terms:description: sorrow is the emotion that is characterized by a long term state of intense sadness, distress and a degree of resignation (not accepting).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sorrow

owl:Class.terms:description: A sound argument is a valid argument with true premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sound argument

owl:Class.terms:description: A sound wave is a mechanical wave that is an oscillation of pressure transmitted through a solid, liquid, or gas, composed of frequencies within the range of hearing.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sound wave

owl:Class.terms:description: A spatial boundary is the closure minus the interior of a subset of a topological space.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: spatial boundary

owl:Class.terms:description: A spatial quantity is a quantity obtained from measuring the spatial extent of an entity
owl:Class.rdfs:label: spatial quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: A spatial region is an object contained in some region of space.
owl:Class.resource:example: The airspace above Ottawa airport; the band around the northern hemisphere between 50 degrees N and 60 degrees N; the spatial region occupied by a bottle.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: spatial region

owl:Class.terms:description: A specification for spatial location is an effective specification towards representation spatial position or spatial data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: spatial specification

owl:Class.terms:description: A specialized material entity is a material entity that is defined by having some quality, role or capability.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: specialized material entity

owl:Class.terms:description: Specific gravity is the ratio of the density of a substance to the density of a reference substance; equivalently, it is the ratio of the mass of a substance to the mass of a reference substance for the same given volume.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: specific gravity

owl:Class.terms:description: A specification is a description of the essential technical attributes/requirements for an object or procedure, and may be used to determine that the object / procedure meets its requirements/attributes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: specification

owl:Class.terms:description: A specimen is a portion of material for use in testing, examination, or study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen

owl:Class.terms:description: speculation is an opinion based on incomplete evidence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: speculation

owl:Class.terms:description: speech is the expression of thoughts and feelings by sound.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: speech

owl:Class.terms:description: Speed is the rate of change of an object's position.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: speed

owl:Class.terms:description: A spherical coordinate system is a coordinate system for three-dimensional space where the position of a point is specified by three numbers: the radial distance of that point from a fixed origin, its polar angle measured from a fixed zenith direction, and the azimuth angle of its orthogonal projection on a reference plane that passes through the origin and is orthogonal to the zenith, measured from a fixed reference direction on that plane.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: spherical coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: A splice site is a region required for the excision of an intron and connection to another exon.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: splice site

owl:Class.terms:description: A stack graph is a statistical graph which presents multiple series in which the distance between one series and another indicates the relative contribution to the total for any x-value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: stack graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A stacked bar graph is a bar graph in which each rectangular bar is partioned by the categorical value of each series of data.
owl:Class.resource:example: Graphs 6,7 in http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: stacked bar graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A standard is a socially-agreed upon specification.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard

owl:Class.terms:description: A standard deviation (represented by the symbol σ) is the quantity of variation from the average (mean, or expected value).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard deviation

owl:Class.terms:description: A standard operating procedure is a specification approved for use in specific environments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard operating procedure

owl:Class.terms:description: A standard score is the (signed) number of standard deviations an observation or datum is above the mean.
owl:Class.resource:hasSynonym: z-value, z-score, normal score, standardadized variable.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard score

owl:Class.terms:description: A start codon is the first codon of a messenger RNA (mRNA) transcript translated by a ribosome. The start codon is almost always preceded by an untranslated region 5' UTR.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: start codon

owl:Class.terms:description: A start date is a time instant pertaining to the date of the beginning of a process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: start date

owl:Class.terms:description: A start point is a terminal point which is the first of an ordered pair of points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: start point

owl:Class.terms:description: A start position is the proximal position of an object relative to an origin in a linear system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: start position

owl:Class.terms:description: A start time is a time instant pertaining to the time at which a process begins.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: start time

owl:Class.terms:description: A state is a set of governing and supportive institutions that have sovereignty over a definite territory and population.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: state

owl:Class.terms:description: A statement is a proposition that is either (a) a meaningful declarative sentence that is either true or false, or (b) that which a true or false declarative sentence asserts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statement

owl:Class.dc:description: a statement of consequence is a statement concerning the result or effect of an action or condition.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statement of consequence

owl:Class.terms:description: A stationary point is a point that is part of a curve in which the derivative at that point is zero, and hence its value is at least a local maximum or minimum.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: stationary point

owl:Class.terms:description: A statistical association is any relationship between two measured quantities that renders them statistically dependent.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statistical association

owl:Class.terms:description: A statistical graph is a figure that displays the relationship among numeric data and/or mathematical functions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statistical graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A statistical graph line is a line used in a statistical graph to communicate some trend or feature of the embedded data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statistical graph line

owl:Class.terms:description: status descriptor is a descriptor for the state of a process or object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: status descriptor

owl:Class.terms:description: A statute is a formal written enactment of a legislative authority that governs a state, city or country.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statute

owl:Class.terms:description: A stereoisomer is an isomer in which the atomic connectivity is the same, but differs in its spatial arrangement of atoms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: stereoisomer

owl:Class.terms:description: A stop codon (or termination codon) is a nucleotide triplet within messenger RNA that signals a termination of translation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: stop codon

owl:Class.terms:description: straight is a quality of a bearer that is free of curves, bends, or angles.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: straight

owl:Class.terms:description: A strain is a genetic variant or kind of microorganism.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: strain

owl:Class.terms:description: A streamgraph is a multi-line stacked graph that yields the appearance of continuous y-values across the x-axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: streamgraph

owl:Class.terms:description: A street name is the token given to identify a particular street.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: street name

owl:Class.terms:description: strong is a qualitative intensity value that is more intense than moderate, but less intense than severe.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: strong

owl:Class.terms:description: A strong submolecular component is a submolecular component that strongly connects submolecular components.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: strong submolecular component

owl:Class.terms:description: A structural isomer is an isomer in which the atoms are joined together in different ways.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: structural isomer

owl:Class.terms:description: A structural motif is a pattern in a structure formed by a spatial arrangement of objects (e.g. atoms).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: structural motif

owl:Class.terms:description: A structural quality is a quality of an object that describes its structure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: structural quality

owl:Class.terms:description: structure is the specification that refers to the composition and arrangement of parts of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: structure

owl:Class.terms:description: A student is an individual who is attends an educational institution.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: student

owl:Class.terms:description: A student advisor role is the role of an individual employed at an academic organization that is involved in advising students.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: student advisor role

owl:Class.terms:description: A student role is the role of an individual that is enrolled in courses at an academic institution.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: student role

owl:Class.terms:description: A study is a process that realizes the steps of a study design.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: study

owl:Class.terms:description: A study design is a protocol for the proper execution of a study which normally requires a carefullly crafted research question or hypothesis and at least one variable under observation and observed values for that variable.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: study design

owl:Class.terms:description: A study group is a group of individuals that are subjects in an observational or intervention study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: study group

owl:Class.terms:description: A study subject is an individual that is the subject of the study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: study subject

owl:Class.terms:description: A subject role is the role of an individual that is the target of the study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: subject role

owl:Class.terms:description: A submolecular entity is a part of a molecular entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: submolecular entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A submolecule is a mereological sum of covalently bonded atoms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: submolecule

owl:Class.terms:description: A substrate is a molecule that is consumed in the course of a biochemical reaction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: substrate

owl:Class.terms:description: The role of a chemical entity that is modified in a chemical reaction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: substrate role

owl:Class.terms:description: Suffering is the unpleasant emotion and aversion associated with the perception of harm or threat of harm in an individual.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: suffering

owl:Class.terms:description: suicidal is the emotion of being deeply unhappy or depressed with thoughts of killing one's self.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: suicidal

owl:Class.terms:description: A sum is the result of adding a set of values together.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sum

owl:Class.terms:description: A supernatent is a liquid substance that remains after centrifugation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: supernatant

owl:Class.terms:description: The surface area of a is a measure of the total area that the surface of the object occupies.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: surface area

owl:Class.terms:description: A surface normal is a vector that is perpendicular to a flat surface.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: surface normal

owl:Class.terms:description: surprise is a brief emotion experienced as the result of an unexpected event.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: surprise

owl:Class.terms:description: suspended is the status of a process that is no longer progressing towards completion.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: suspended

owl:Class.terms:description: A syllable is a verbal entity of language having one vowel sound, with or without surrounding consonants, forming the whole or a part of a word.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: syllable

owl:Class.terms:description: A symbol is a proposition about what an entity represents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: symbol

owl:Class.terms:description: symport enabled secondary active transport is a secondary active transfort in which both ion and molecule are transported in the same direction simultaneously.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: symport enabled secondary active transport

owl:Class.terms:description: A syndrome is composed of a set of several clinically recognizable features, signs (observed by someone other than the patient), symptoms (reported by the patient), phenomena or characteristics that often occur together.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: syndrome

owl:Class.terms:description: A synonym is a word with the same or very similar meanings.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: synonym

owl:Class.terms:description: A synthesis reaction is an inorganic reaction in which two or more molecules are chemically bonded together to produce a single product.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: synthesis reaction

owl:Class.terms:description: A t-statistic is a ratio of the departure of an estimated parameter from its notional value and its standard error.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: t-statistic

owl:Class.terms:description: A t-statistic based decreased differential gene expression is a differential gene expression ratio in which the t-statistic is less than zero.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: t-statistic based decreased differential gene expression

owl:Class.terms:description: A t-statistic based increased differential gene expression is a differential gene expression ratio in which the t-statistic is greater than zero.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: t-statistic based increased differential gene expression

owl:Class.terms:description: A table is a figure that consists of an ordered arrangement of columns and rows.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: table

owl:Class.terms:description: The table of contents is a document section that lists all sections (and optionally subsections) in a sequential order along with their page number.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: table of contents

owl:Class.terms:description: A tag cloud is a visualization of word frequencies.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: tag cloud

owl:Class.terms:description: A technical report is a publication published by a school or other institution, usually numbered within a series.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: technical report

owl:Class.terms:description: The telephone is a communications device that transmits and receives sounds, and are minimally composed of a microphone to speak into, a speaker'which reproduces the voice of the other person and a ringer which makes a sound to alert the owner when a call is coming in.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: telephone

owl:Class.terms:description: a telephone number is an identifier used to connect to a physical device capable of transfering voice or data over a network.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: telephone number

owl:Class.terms:description: A television program is a audiovisual media that is produced and broadcast using a television.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: television program

owl:Class.terms:description: a temporal qualifier is pertains to the frequency of the event of interest.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: temporal qualifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A term is a word or phrase used to denote one or more entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: term

owl:Class.terms:description: A term variant is a term that is a variant of another term.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: term variant

owl:Class.terms:description: A terminal point is a point that defines the finite extension of a line.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: terminal point

owl:Class.dc:description: A terminology is a set of terms used for a specified application.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: terminology

owl:Class.terms:description: A territory is a non-sovereign geographic region.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: territory

owl:Class.terms:description: terror is the extreme feeling of fear.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: terror

owl:Class.terms:description: A tertiary structure descriptor describes 3D topological patterns in a biopolymer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: tertiary structure descriptor

owl:Class.terms:description: A test role is the role of an individual that is a participant in the study and is the target of the intervention.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: test role

owl:Class.terms:description: text quality is the quality of a textual entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: text quality

owl:Class.terms:description: A text span is a subset of contiguous sequence of characters of a textual entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: text span

owl:Class.terms:description: text span end position is the position (offset) of the last character of a text span in relation the text it is from.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: text span end position

owl:Class.terms:description: text span start position is the position (offset) of the first character of a text span in relation the text it is from.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: text span start position

owl:Class.terms:description: A textual chart is a chart containing text.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: textual chart

owl:Class.terms:description: A textual entity is language entity that is manifested as a sequence of one or more distinct characters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: textual entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene disease association in which the gene is a therapeutic marker for the disease.
owl:Class.resource:hasSynonym: gene-disease association arising from a therapeutic role of the gene/protein
owl:Class.rdfs:label: therapeutic gene-disease association

owl:Class.terms:description: A thesis document is the written research component of a post-secondary institution that contains a statement supported by arguments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: thesis document

owl:Class.terms:description: thickness is the shortest dimensional extent of a 3D projection of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: thickness

owl:Class.terms:description: A tick mark is a line segment that is spatially positioned perpendicular to the axis of a statistical graph and indicates the position of a specific numeric value (which may be indicated by an adjacent value label) on a value axis, or is one of a pair of tick marks that delineates the boundary of a categorical value (which may be indicated by an adjacent category label) on the categorical axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: tick mark

owl:Class.terms:description: A time instant is a temporal region which occurs instantaneously, e.g. having no duration.
owl:Class.resource:example: at this moment; the moment at which a finger is detached in an industrial accident; the moment at which a child is born; the moment of death
owl:Class.rdfs:label: time instant

owl:Class.terms:description: A time internval is a contiguous temporal region having some duration.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: time interval

owl:Class.terms:description: time measurement is a measurement value of the duration of some interval of time or a particular instant of time (against some frame of reference).
owl:Class.schema:comment: Time intervals are specified as date/datetime ranges.
owl:Class.resource:example: the duration of my life; the duration of a surgical procedure, the moment of death
owl:Class.rdfs:label: time measurement

owl:Class.terms:description: A tissue is a mereologically maximal collection of cells that together perform some function.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: tissue

owl:Class.terms:description: A title is a textual entity that summarily describes some entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: title

owl:Class.terms:description: to actively interact with is the capability to interact with another entity in a way that requires physical contact.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to actively interact with

owl:Class.terms:description: to add a covalent bond is the capability to covalently modify a chemical entity by adding a covalent bond.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to add a covalent bond

owl:Class.terms:description: to assemble is the capability to combine entities together into a larger object that persists in time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to assemble

owl:Class.terms:description: to associate is the capability to physically interact with another object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to associate

owl:Class.terms:description: to be a member of is the capability to be considered a part of a collection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be a member of

owl:Class.terms:description: to be a part of is the capability to be assembled into a larger structure that persists in time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be a part of

owl:Class.terms:description: to be activated is the capability to be modified in such a way that the conformational change leads to an increase in another capability.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be activated

owl:Class.terms:description: to be actively interacted with is the capability to be manipulated by some device or agent.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be actively interacted with

owl:Class.terms:description: to be cleaved is the capability to be modified in a way that splits one part of the object from the other.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be cleaved

owl:Class.terms:description: to be combined is the capability to be modified in a way that the object is merged with another object to form a new object or substance.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be combined

owl:Class.terms:description: to be compared is the capability of an object to be examined in order to note the similarities or differences among a set of objects.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be compared

owl:Class.terms:description: to be conformationally changed is the capability to be modified in such a way that the object's conformation is changed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be conformationally changed

owl:Class.terms:description: to be covalently modified is the capability of a chemical entity to have bonds added or removed
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be covalently modified

owl:Class.terms:description: to be electronically modified is the capability of a chemical entity to have electrons added or removed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be electronically modified

owl:Class.terms:description: to be examined is the capability of an object to be observed in a detailed manner.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be examined

owl:Class.terms:description: to be inhibited is the capability to be modified in such a way that the conformational change leads to an decrease in another capability.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be inhibited

owl:Class.terms:description: to be interacted with is the capability of an object to be target of a physical interaction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be interacted with

owl:Class.terms:description: to be modified is the capability to be actively interacted with in such a way that it leads to a physical reconfiguration.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be modified

owl:Class.terms:description: to be observed is the capability of an object to be perceived.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be observed

owl:Class.terms:description: to be passively interacted with is the capability of an object to be observed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be passively interacted with

owl:Class.terms:description: to be recorded is the capability of an object to be observed in such a way that information about it can be transcribed in a specified format on some physical medium.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be recorded

owl:Class.terms:description: to be translocated is the capability to be physically displaced from one location to another
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be translocated

owl:Class.terms:description: to be transported is the disposition to undergo motion.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be transported

owl:Class.terms:description: to bind to is the capability to physically interact with another object through a set of non-covalent interactions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: to bind to
